net.proteusframework.data.filesystem

Class StreamStorage

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.data.filesystem.StreamStorage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, NamedObject, FileEntityStorage
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DatabaseStreamStorage, NativeStreamStorage

    @Entity
public abstract class StreamStorage
extends Object
implements FileEntityStorage, NamedObject, Serializable

    Defines an interface for storing data for FileEntity instances. All methods should be expected to block until complete, perhaps for long periods of time. If responsiveness is an issue the caller must make arrangements for background execution.

    The FileEntity.getStreamId() property may be maintained by implementations to identify the data and should be treated as opaque by code outside of the particular StreamStorage implementation in use.

    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • getLocationSummary

        public abstract String getLocationSummary(FileEntity file)
        Get the location summary for the stream. This method is intended for diagnostic purposes, such as error reporting. The intended audience is developers and system administrators. Enough information must be provided such that the data may be found quickly and precisely. Examples include "Database in table stream, record 53", "/mnt/share/path/file-5112.jpg", etc.
        Parameters:
        file - the file.
        Returns:
